The summary data has been taken from the trip level aggregation, to the driver and vehicle level. Individual trip IDs are no longer carried over.</font></div></div></div>" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontSize=11;" parent="WIyWlLk6GJQsqaUBKTNV-1" vertex="1"> div.font: The SHRP2 NDS time series data and the map matching information are brought together to form trip level summaries for each timestep in the trip. The distance traveled for each timestep was calculated based on vehicle speed and trip variables such as the speed, speeding, headway, following distance, and others were binned to appropriate values. A group summary was performed to aggregate miles driven over the variable combinations.

div.font: The trip level summary data is combined with vehicle information and driver demographics from the SHRP2 study to aggregate the data at the driver and vehicle level. Total miles driven for the selected variable - speeding - and the relevant roadway characteristics were calculated for the known driver demographics and vehicle information.
